{@--3@} 
Explanatory repetition or 
reference to what is already 
mentioned, such as paraphrase or free
translation; particularly, any 
portion of the Brāhmaṇas which 
comments on, illustrates, or explains a
{%Vidhi%} or direction previously laid
down and which does not itself
lay down any directions; a 
supplementary repetition, <ab>opp.</ab> to {#viDi#} 
‘authoritative or direct injunction’;
{#viDivihitasya anuvacanamanuvAdaH .#} 
{#nAnuvAdapunaruktayoH viSezaH SabdAByAsopapatteH#} <ls>Nyāya Sūtra</ls>.
It is of {3} kinds:--{#BUtArTa°#} ({#sadeva#} 

{#sOmyedamagra AsIt#}); {#stutyarTa°#} ({#vAyurvE kzepizWA devatA#})
and {#guRa°#} ({#agnihotraM juhoti ityukte daDnA#}
{#juhoti iti guRaviDAnAMt#}); see {#arTavAda#}
also.
